race.comment: DEEP STEALTH (4) has looked the winner in the straight at her last two runs, both over longer trips. Gets the run of the race from gate one and coming back to 1175m appears ideal. Should grab a well-deserved win in a race that sets up perfectly. DIZZY DEE (2) relished the heavy going when she led all the way to win a similar race to this here eight days ago. Handles all conditions and makes her own luck up front so she looks a genuine hope again. ULTIMATE SAY (5) was there when they cornered but failed to let down first-up over 1106m here. Will benefit greatly from that hit-out and should be right in the mix. KEVIN MCKEEN (3) picked up nicely to grab second when resuming in a Class 3 over 1015m here recently. Won't find this as tough and the extra trip suits so he looks well placed. WELCOME BACK (8) has won just once in 66 runs but can sneak into the minor end of the prize.
